"A shawl (from Persian: \u0634\u0627\u0644\u200e sh\u0101l, which may be from Hindi: \u0926\u0941\u0936\u093e\u0932\u093e du\u015b\u0101l\u0101, ultimately from Sanskrit: \u0936\u093e\u091f\u0940 \u015b\u0101\u1e6d\u012b) is a simple item of clothing, loosely worn over the shoulders, upper body and arms, and sometimes also over the head. It is usually a rectangular or square piece of cloth, which is often folded to make a triangle, but can also be triangular in shape. Other shapes include oblong shawls."